Understory Net Audit — third-party attribution
================================================

The following open-source projects were STUDIED for BEHAVIOR ONLY during the
design of the DNS-filter tunnel, connection-visibility, and per-app attribution
features. No source code from these projects is copied into this repository —
every corresponding implementation here is an independent, clean-room
reimplementation. They are credited here in good faith.

RethinkDNS (https://github.com/celzero/rethink-dns)
  Licensed under the Apache License 2.0.
  Copyright RethinkDNS and its authors.
  Studied for: the on-device DNS-blocklist matching approach (a compressed trie
  answering "is this domain blocked?"; our clean-room implementation uses a
  simpler domain-suffix HashSet — see net-engine/DnsBlocklist.kt), the
  per-flow app attribution via ConnectivityManager.getConnectionOwnerUid (see
  firewall/tunnel/ConnectionAttributor.kt), the DNS-only VpnService tun
  establishment pattern, and the NXDOMAIN/zero-IP sinkhole answer.

PCAPdroid (https://github.com/emanuele-f/PCAPdroid)
  Licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.
  Copyright 2020-2021 Emanuele Faranda.
  Studied for: the connection-log data model and the DNS-query→connection
  association approach (our clean-room event log is a lean domain+app+verdict
  ring buffer — see firewall/tunnel/DnsEventLog.kt). No GPL code is included.

InviZible Pro (https://github.com/Gedsh/InviZible)
  Licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.
  Studied for: the unprivileged daemon subprocess (ProcessStarter) pattern for
  running DNSCrypt/Tor. Understory does NOT ship such daemons; encrypted-
  resolver routing is a documented, unimplemented stub (see
  firewall/tunnel/DnsFilterTun.kt). No GPL code is included.

de1984 (https://github.com/…/de1984)
  Studied for: the slot-free ConnectivityManager per-app firewall backend
  (Android 13+ `cmd connectivity` OEM_DENY_3 chain) and the UID-exemption
  safety gate. Reimplemented over Understory's own Shizuku broker (see
  firewall/policy/ConnectivityManagerBackend.kt, policy/UidExemptions.kt).

Bundled blocklist
  firewall/src/main/assets/blocklist/base.hosts.gz is a small, curated SEED of
  well-known ad/tracker/malware domain roots, hand-authored for this project
  (not copied verbatim from any single public list). It is user-updatable from
  an https:// blocklist URL of the user's choosing.
